\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10954091 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14754656\charrsid3559264 Oh - that I can't - I can't remember. But I think in them days we used to have plenty of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4072492\charrsid3559264 Quaker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14754656\charrsid3559264  oats. Porridge, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12139752 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14754656\charrsid3559264 What would you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10954091 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14754656\charrsid3559264 Oh tea. We never know what coffee was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12139752 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14754656\charrsid3559264 Did you have anything different on any certain days like Sunday?
