Oh he would. Oh he - he'd look after everything - as far as I'm aware of anyway 'cos - I know in winter he had to go out pretty early - he had to go out early in the mornings, was dark in them days in the morning. Well then
 he - he left the responsibility to another person, a friend of ours - used to live a few doors away, I don't know but - that I - I know he used to go up and feed 'em when he come home from work. But as - as feeding in the morning I can't exactly tell you
 that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12139752 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14754656\charrsid3559264 But your father really looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10954091 RM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14754656\charrsid3559264 Yes.
